select* from student;
select* 
from student
where age > 20 and gender = 'Female';

image = Day3/image.png
where clause is used for all the operations like :- arithmetic operations, comparison operations, and logical operations.


some type to operatros :
1) and
2) or
3) not --- not is for not inside the condition, eg where not age > 20; 
-- another long example : where not (age > 20 and gender = 'Female');

some more types are like :-
1) in --- eg where age in (20, 21, 22);
2) between --- eg where age between 20 and 25;
3) like --- eg where name like 'A%'; (A% means any name starting with A)
4) not in --- eg where age not in (20, 21, 22);

limit --- eg limit 5; - limits the whole table to 5 records

order by --- eg order by age asc; (asc - ascending order, desc - descending order)  

select *
from student
order by age asc;

question - to show the age of the only top 5 students
solution - select * from student order by age asc limit 5;


    
